annotation.TEXT: Maybe I should stop flying up so we can actually see these guys' names.
BGM: Wario Land (GB) - Stage Theme VII
There's Neidave.
Yes, you can safely pass through loose ceiling spikes (or skulls in this case) before they actually start falling. (I learned this while playing Touhou Mario.)
Oh, and all of a sudden, there's the goal, with unfortunately no real means to hit the top of it... Well, that sucks for my goal tape average...
And there's the P-switch. Okay, so first, I'll clear the way forward, then I'll go for the Yoshi coin.
Okay, now the other hidden 1-up that I missed was apparently a checkpoint 1-up, which requires me to move from right to left on this log...

Yep, there's a feather and a 1-up up there, and there's also some enemies below that I can't see from here, and with all of those sprites, I cannot get the vine to appear. But, maybe if I can shell jump up to those items...
Agus anois, cluiche b√≥nas luas ludicrous.
Okay, that turn block is either a multi-coin block or a vine. I'm thinking a vine.

Yep. I think what should be done is have the 1-up and feather up there be in ? blocks or turn blocks (have one of them act like a green ! block for the feather). This way, those items won't be sprites until the player gets up there and opens them. Also, this Yoshi coin below is extremely tricky to get safely. Maybe extend the ledge the player needs to land on one space further to the left.
Ah, there we go. Now, if I can't get back out, I'll rewind. Oh, but I can certainly get back out.
Huh. I can pass through the thin platform from below.
Uh, oh. I've spent too much time fooling around.
Well, those stairs lead nowhere, but at least I can't fall to my death there.
To be continued...

...Or, it could be neither... Umm... You know what? I think that block was supposed to have a vine, but the sprite limit somehow interfered. But, what sprites were present? There's the Boo Ring, the shell, and an earlier springboard. That's all I'm aware of. Let me do some experimenting here...
Bah, not quite, but I know I can do it...
Hmm... Is there anything over there in the upper-right? Because that looks suspicious.
It's getting tricky once again.
Made it! Now, if I hit that block down there after collecting these items, the vine should appear.
96-coin combo!
Oh, there's the goal. Better take aim at the top of it!
Umm... Dudes? Wanna get out of my way please?
Alright, fine. I'll go up here first.
Yay, another mushroom that I don't need right now.
BGM: Cave Story - Last Battle
Yeah, I bet these Red Beetles are actually Spinies, right?
Hello, and welcome back to COLLAB! Up next is Red Beetle Cave, so let's-a-go!
Okay, forget it. I'll just slide-kill these guys over here instead.
Oh, it's MarioFanGamer659. He's the one who suggested that I play this hack in the first place.
Okay, with some off screen looking around (with a little bit of rewind assistance), I've figured out the problem. There are additional sprites nearby that I just couldn't see.
Goal tape average so far: 423 / 11 = 38.455 stars each.
Whoa, that was close! I did indeed barely have enough time!
Well, I managed to trigger it, so there you go! I'm outta here!

I think I'm done with every level now, unless maybe I missed some Yoshi coins or something somewhere... (I only found three Yoshi coins in Haunted Home. Is that all that are there?) However, I'm not quite done with this hack yet!

Yep, it's the Big Boo Boss, which I'll barely have enough time to defeat (it takes a minimum of 30 SMW seconds to get the job done, so entering with 31 or more seconds is required in order to not run out of time).
You're welcome!
I got all of the Yoshi coins, but I'm not done yet. Is this gonna be the Big Boo Boss?
Oh, I can stand on the darker clouds. Hmm... Is it possible for me to go over the top here with some Boo assistance?
Nuts. Well, maybe I wasn't high enough.
Okay, hurry up! I don't have time to slip up now!
Found it! However, I really don't know about that positioning. What if a player trying to jump over an Eerie gets screwed over by it?
Okay, I'm going to try to slide kill this thing just to get revenge... if I can.
Nope, although I did manage to get double coins from two of the blocks.
BGM: Luigi's Mansion: Dark Moon - Gloomy Manor
Okay, with that short level completed, I now head to Haunted Fortress. This might be the last real level, since this is only a one-world hack.
Bonus game average so far: 29 / 4 = 7.25 1-ups each.
Whoa! How did I get enough momentum to slide all the way up and over that steep slope?!
D'oh! That thing managed to nibble on the extreme corner of my shoe...
And, I guess that's it. However, before I end the video, I want to revisit Living Death Mine for a moment. Apparently, there's a couple of hidden 1-ups that I wasn't aware of in there...
Replace "enemys" with "enemies".
Are there any reset doors or pipes in case a player goes for the Yoshi coin first and then doesn't make it back in time to clear out the other path? I just had to ask that.
Yep. Oh, there's another Pokey Boo over there, which I can easily slide-kill.
This looks like a part of the first level, except with some additional pipes down here and the hands on the clocks spinning around like crazy.
Thank goodness for my cape. Otherwise, who knows how long I'd need to wait for the winged platform and Boo Ring opening to line up...
Ooh, but I happened to get a 1-up for lining up the digits in the stars and timer!
Yeah, I'm just fooling around. Let's get back to business here.
This is going to be the whole video right here, folks... Nah, just kidding.
That was kind of cool, but also a waste of valuable time!
Goal tape average so far: 383 / 10 = 38.3 stars each.

It seems weird to require the player to either shell jump or fly with a cape in order to reach the Yoshi coin that was up there. (Although, I guess requiring cape flight would be less weird if capes were more common in this hack.)
Nope, nothing. Although, I did get a glimpse of a Yoshi coin that I'll need a P-switch for.
Huh, I wonder why the screen is allowed to scroll up here? Did you forget to turn off vertical scrolling here? Or is there a secret of some sort up there?
BGM: ???
"Credits", eh? So, I guess that means I've beaten the game...
Oh, the cape is so handy for this. Now, I guess the first 1-up is just randomly hidden somewhere during the first skull raft ride...
I wonder what's in this turn block? Is there a shell or something nearby that I can hit it with?
Also, there's the rising and falling background, too.
Can't fly up there. Munchers are in the way. Not that there's any reason to fly up there anyway.
Oh, that's neat. I managed to make my horizontal speed exactly match the autoscrolling speed while I'm in the middle of the screen. Let's see how long I can maintain this.
Space-time rewind count: 4
Do any of these blocks contain a power up that I could use?
Aww... If I didn't waste time trying to slide-kill that other beetle, I could've gotten this 1-up.
Or, maybe a gray platform that didn't appear the first time because I was apparently at the sprite limit a moment ago for some reason? Also, this turn block contains a vine. Umm... Why?
